   District of Nevada U.S.B.C.Services Offered by the Court

   Subject:
   Docket Information for Las Vegas and Reno Through PACER

   The public may receive case information through the PACER web site at
   http://pacer.nvb.uscourts.gov or by clicking on the PACER button on our
   web page.
   What information is available on PACER?
   PACER provides access to federal case information nationwide. The PACER
   system offers quick, accurate information about current federal cases.
   You can obtain:
   * A listing of all parties and participants including judges, attorneys
   and trustees
   * A compilation of case related information such as cause of action,
   nature of suit and dollar demand
   * A chronology of dates of case events entered in the case record
   * A claims registry
   * A listing of new cases each day in the bankruptcy courts
   * Appellate court opinions
   * Judgments or case status
   * Types of documents filed for certain cases
   * Beginning approximately January 15, 2002 images of documents will
   also be available.
   How can I search a PACER database?
   You may search by case number, party name or filing date range in the
   U.S. District courts. You may search by case number or party name in
   the U.S. Court of Appeals and Bankruptcy Courts.
   Fees for PACER
   The PACER/RACER Service Center will charge all registered agencies or
   individuals $0.07 per page. Users must register before accessing
   information. This may be done through the Pacer/Racer Service Center
   website at http://pacer.psc.uscourts.gov or by calling the PACER/RACER
   Service Center at (800) 676-6856, 8:00 a.m. - 5:00 p.m. CST (Monday -
   Friday).
   For More "Frequently Asked Pacer Questions, click on
   http://pacer.psc.uscourts.gov/faq.html
